translated: Engfeldt, Fritz Henrik was a provincial physician from Gislaved. He was born on January 14, 1892 in Malmö to Reverend J.O. Engfeldt and Pauline Olsson. He married Gunhild Xenia Zanders in 1922, and they had two children: Elsa Britt, born in 1923 and died in 1944, and Torsten Fredrik, born in 1927. Engfeldt received his high school diploma from Ystad in 1911, his Bachelor of Medicine in 1915, and his medical license in 1921 from Stockholm. He worked as a resident physician at Västervik Hospital from 1916-1918, at Jönköping Hospital in 1918, in the Jörns district in 1919, and at St. Göran's Hospital Influenza Department in 1920. He was a temporary assistant physician at Katarina Hospital in Stockholm from 1921-1922, a second assistant physician at Jönköping Hospital from 1922-1923, and a first assistant physician there from 1923-1925, during which he served as temporary chief physician for three months. Engfeldt was appointed as a provincial physician in the Gislaved district in 1925 and served as the medical examiner in Gislaved from 1926. He also served as a field medical intern from 1921-1924 and served with the old troop regiment. From 1924-1925, he served as a battalion physician at Fik. Engfeldt was a member of the municipal board and school board.
